WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.360
allahu akbar, alhamdulillah, rabbil ʿalamin,

00:00:07.360 --> 00:00:12.100
ar-rahmāni, ar-raḥīn, mālik yawm al-deen,

00:00:12.100 --> 00:00:16.600
hiyā ka n'aʿbud wa hiyā ka nastahīn,

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:19.600
ehdīn al-sirāṭa l-mustaqīm,

00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:22.800
sirāṭa l-ladīn anʿamta ʿalayhim,

00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:32.320
ghayri l-mawdūb ʿalayhim.

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:35.720
As-salāmu ʿalaykum wa ʿarḥmatu ʿAllāhi wa ʿbarakātu.

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:38.920
بسم الله والحمد لله والصلاة والسلام

00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:40.820
على عبد الله ورسوله محمد

00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:43.620
وعلى آله وأصحابه أجمعين

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:46.120
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:00:46.120 --> 00:00:47.920
We thank Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:50.820
for giving us this beautiful month of Ramadan.

00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:51.720
And as you know,

00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.320
the month of Ramadan is the month of the Quran.

00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:56.720
It is the month where we study the Quran,

00:00:56.720 --> 00:00:59.020
we listen to it, we try to understand it,

00:00:59.020 --> 00:01:02.320
we put it into practice and we convey it to others.

00:01:02.320 --> 00:01:05.720
Every deed that we engage in in this month is multiplied.

00:01:05.720 --> 00:01:07.020
You and I know that.

00:01:07.020 --> 00:01:09.720
A farad act, the reward of it is multiplied.

00:01:09.720 --> 00:01:11.720
A sunnah act, the reward of it

00:01:11.720 --> 00:01:14.420
gets right up to a farad and perhaps beyond,

00:01:14.420 --> 00:01:15.720
depending on your intention.

00:01:15.720 --> 00:01:17.720
My beloved brothers and sisters,

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:19.520
we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:21.020
to make us from amongst those

00:01:21.020 --> 00:01:22.920
who take this month seriously.

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:23.820
For it is a gift,

00:01:23.820 --> 00:01:26.020
it might be the last Ramadan

00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:27.920
we are going to see in our lives.

00:01:27.920 --> 00:01:30.320
And we have seen Ramadans in the past.

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:32.120
We are lucky to see tonight

00:01:32.120 --> 00:01:35.020
if Allah wants, we may not see tomorrow night.

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:36.920
And this is the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:39.920
In the past, my beloved brothers and sisters,

00:01:39.920 --> 00:01:41.720
we have been through translation

00:01:41.720 --> 00:01:44.720
of various verses of the Quran.

00:01:44.720 --> 00:01:46.420
And we have been through

00:01:46.420 --> 00:01:47.720
the reasons of revelations

00:01:47.720 --> 00:01:50.720
of the verses of the Quran in brief.

00:01:50.720 --> 00:01:52.120
And we have been through

00:01:52.120 --> 00:01:54.120
stories of the Prophets.

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:55.120
We have been through

00:01:55.120 --> 00:01:57.220
subjects within the noble Quran

00:01:57.220 --> 00:01:58.720
over the years.

00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:02.320
And this year, as you would perhaps know,

00:02:02.320 --> 00:02:05.820
we have to complete the stories of the Prophets

00:02:05.820 --> 00:02:08.320
by the story of the greatest of all Prophets

00:02:08.320 --> 00:02:10.120
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:02:10.120 --> 00:02:12.320
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:13.920
So it was only befitting

00:02:13.920 --> 00:02:16.220
that we dedicated the entire month

00:02:16.220 --> 00:02:18.020
to the story of this messenger,

00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:19.420
peace be upon him.

00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:21.820
Whereas when it came to the other messengers,

00:02:21.820 --> 00:02:24.620
a night or two or three was enough.

00:02:24.620 --> 00:02:25.920
When it comes to Rasulullah

00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:27.520
salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:02:27.520 --> 00:02:29.220
we being his ummah,

00:02:29.220 --> 00:02:30.920
it is only befitting

00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:32.720
that we take our time

00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:33.920
to go through the life

00:02:33.920 --> 00:02:36.320
of the most blessed of all creatures,

00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:38.520
the high and the loftiest in rank

00:02:38.520 --> 00:02:41.220
of all the creatures of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:02:41.220 --> 00:02:43.120
We ask Allah to grant us

00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:46.620
the understanding of the gift that we have.

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:48.920
The gift that we have of being mu'mineen,

00:02:48.920 --> 00:02:50.720
believing in Allah alone.

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:53.420
The gift that we have of being the ummah

00:02:53.420 --> 00:02:55.620
of the highest of creation.

00:02:55.620 --> 00:02:58.620
These are two gifts of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:02:58.620 --> 00:03:01.820
that He selects and chooses people to give them.

00:03:01.820 --> 00:03:03.720
So we have been carefully chosen

00:03:03.720 --> 00:03:05.620
by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:07.620
to give us this gift of His.

00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:09.920
And wallahi, if we look at it

00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:11.420
and if we understand it,

00:03:11.420 --> 00:03:14.320
we will be able to recognize a gift of Allah

00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:17.220
and become the beloved of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:19.720
May Allah make us those who love Him

00:03:19.720 --> 00:03:22.020
and may He love us in return.

00:03:22.020 --> 00:03:23.020
Ameen.

00:03:23.020 --> 00:03:25.020
My beloved brothers and sisters,

00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:26.720
it is very important for us

00:03:26.720 --> 00:03:28.920
to go through an introduction.

00:03:28.920 --> 00:03:31.720
And this introduction would start with

00:03:31.720 --> 00:03:33.720
the importance of learning

00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:36.520
the history of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:39.420
What does it do and what will it do to me

00:03:39.420 --> 00:03:42.920
if I study the life of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:03:42.920 --> 00:03:44.420
Point number one.

00:03:44.420 --> 00:03:46.920
The first point that I want to raise.

00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:51.220
It increases my love for him sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:03:51.220 --> 00:03:52.520
And at the same time,

00:03:52.520 --> 00:03:55.020
it increases my love for his maker

00:03:55.020 --> 00:03:57.020
who has made me as well.

00:03:57.020 --> 00:03:58.720
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:00.720
So by studying the seerah,

00:04:00.720 --> 00:04:04.120
by studying the life of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:05.420
and his history,

00:04:05.420 --> 00:04:08.420
it will increase our love for Allah and His rasool.

00:04:08.420 --> 00:04:11.120
We will understand how Allah has chosen

00:04:11.120 --> 00:04:13.320
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:17.520
and how we were chosen to be from amongst his followers.

00:04:17.520 --> 00:04:20.520
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has blessed us

00:04:20.520 --> 00:04:21.620
as Allah says

00:04:32.120 --> 00:04:34.520
Allah has favored the believers

00:04:34.520 --> 00:04:38.020
by sending to them a messenger from amongst them.

00:04:38.020 --> 00:04:41.620
يَتْلُوا عَلَيْهِمْ آيَاتِهِ

00:04:41.620 --> 00:04:44.220
Reading and reciting his verses.

00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:45.220
He came down,

00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:47.120
he did not bring anything from his pocket.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:48.020
Allah says

00:04:51.020 --> 00:04:54.920
He did not utter anything from his desires or lusts or fancies.

00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:04.720
Everything he said was revealed and inspired by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:08.020
Sometimes you will find Allah admonished him.

00:05:08.020 --> 00:05:10.520
Not because he said something from his pocket,

00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:13.320
but because Allah inspired him to say something

00:05:13.320 --> 00:05:15.620
for us to learn later on.

00:05:15.620 --> 00:05:17.420
That if you were to make an error

00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:20.720
or if you were to say something that required admonition,

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:24.120
how should you react to that admonition?

00:05:24.120 --> 00:05:26.320
A lot of us feel bad when we are told.

00:05:26.320 --> 00:05:28.720
A lot of us feel very bad when we are told.

00:05:28.720 --> 00:05:32.120
We will go through the life of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:36.320
and see how he the perfect reacted when he was corrected

00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:39.420
and when he was told may Allah make us from those who follow.

00:05:39.420 --> 00:05:40.520
Remember one thing,

00:05:40.520 --> 00:05:47.220
we always harp on about how important it is to follow the messenger sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:50.320
How will we know it if we haven't gone through his life?

00:05:50.320 --> 00:05:51.220
Subhanallah.

00:05:51.220 --> 00:05:53.820
Can I know how important it is

00:05:53.820 --> 00:05:58.520
or can I know what to do in order to follow Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam's message

00:05:58.520 --> 00:06:00.920
if I don't even know how he reacted?

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:03.120
So this is the beauty of studying the Seerah.

00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:04.720
It draws you closer to Allah.

00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:06.320
It makes you a proper Muslim.

00:06:06.320 --> 00:06:09.520
It makes you a person who is now able to surrender

00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:11.920
after he has read, after he has listened,

00:06:11.920 --> 00:06:13.820
after he or she has understood.

00:06:13.820 --> 00:06:16.220
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:06:16.220 --> 00:06:18.820
Then we will follow his example.

00:06:18.820 --> 00:06:22.220
And at the same time, our love for him will increase.

00:06:22.220 --> 00:06:26.320
And at the same time, our love for his companions will increase

00:06:26.320 --> 00:06:30.120
because they were ready to give up their lives for the sake of Allah.

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:34.620
In fact, many of them gave their lives up for the sake of Allah.

00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:41.320
Allah says in Surah Al-Ahzab,

00:06:41.820 --> 00:06:50.220
من المؤمنين رجال صدقوا ما عاهدوا الله عليه

00:06:50.220 --> 00:06:54.220
فمنهم منقضا نحبه

00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:58.820
ومنهم إن ينتظر

00:06:58.820 --> 00:07:01.820
وما بدلوا تبديلا

00:07:01.820 --> 00:07:05.620
From amongst the men, from amongst the believers,

00:07:05.620 --> 00:07:09.520
they are men who have fulfilled their promise to Allah.

00:07:09.520 --> 00:07:13.720
They have been truthful upon their word to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:07:13.720 --> 00:07:14.820
What they promised Allah?

00:07:14.820 --> 00:07:15.920
We'll give our lives.

00:07:15.920 --> 00:07:17.920
Some of them have already given their lives

00:07:17.920 --> 00:07:19.420
and the others are in waiting.

00:07:19.420 --> 00:07:22.520
This verse was revealed at the time of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam.

00:07:22.520 --> 00:07:24.620
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala help us

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:28.020
to sacrifice at least a bit of our time in the month of Ramadan

00:07:28.020 --> 00:07:31.520
and outside Ramadan as well, at least to fulfill our salah.

00:07:31.520 --> 00:07:34.320
A few days ago, someone was showing me how

00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:38.120
people have been dying in most blessed positions of salah.

00:07:38.220 --> 00:07:41.220
One man in ruku'a, one man as he's starting salah,

00:07:41.220 --> 00:07:46.420
one man on the mimbar just before he got on the musallah

00:07:46.420 --> 00:07:49.520
to be the leader of Salatul Jumu'ah.

00:07:49.520 --> 00:07:51.720
He passed away in this country.

00:07:51.720 --> 00:07:54.820
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant him Jannah.

00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:57.620
But the question is we listen about people

00:07:57.620 --> 00:08:00.720
who have passed away in positions of salah.

00:08:00.720 --> 00:08:03.220
Do we even read our salah to start with?

00:08:03.220 --> 00:08:04.320
That's the question.

00:08:04.320 --> 00:08:06.320
Do we even read our salah?

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:10.820
So what chances do we have to die in the position of sujood

00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:12.820
when we don't even make that sajda?

00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:15.720
By learning the seerah of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:08:15.720 --> 00:08:20.020
we will become regular with our duties unto Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:23.620
because we will see how they achieved success

00:08:23.620 --> 00:08:26.820
through following the messenger salallahu alayhi wasalam.

00:08:26.820 --> 00:08:29.420
This afternoon, I spoke in Jumu'ah

00:08:29.420 --> 00:08:34.220
and I mentioned something very important, Salatul Jumu'ah.

00:08:34.220 --> 00:08:38.520
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has blessed us in every single way.

00:08:38.520 --> 00:08:41.420
We have the seerah of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam.

00:08:41.420 --> 00:08:43.420
We have the month of Ramadan.

00:08:43.420 --> 00:08:46.720
If we don't make use of this, wallahi it carries on.

00:08:46.720 --> 00:08:50.020
We are the ones who missed the train.

00:08:50.020 --> 00:08:54.220
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala also has made mention

00:08:54.220 --> 00:08:58.120
the various details of the life of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam.

00:08:58.120 --> 00:09:03.620
Every detail, the names, the places, his childhood,

00:09:03.620 --> 00:09:06.420
his adulthood and so on.

00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:11.720
Today, we have superheroes and to mention some of them,

00:09:11.720 --> 00:09:15.020
in fact, this is the house of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:09:15.020 --> 00:09:19.020
But we all know that the football stars, we know them.

00:09:19.020 --> 00:09:20.620
Our children know them.

00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:23.420
They know who are their girlfriends astaghfirullah.

00:09:23.420 --> 00:09:25.820
They know the whole history of the golfer,

00:09:25.820 --> 00:09:27.920
that one of the top golfers in the world.

00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:29.020
What happened to him?

00:09:29.020 --> 00:09:31.220
What were the names of the women in his life

00:09:31.220 --> 00:09:33.520
and what exactly he did and they did?

00:09:33.520 --> 00:09:36.320
They know everyone and they know so much of them.

00:09:36.320 --> 00:09:37.620
They know their team.

00:09:37.620 --> 00:09:40.020
They wear the t-shirts of the team.

00:09:40.020 --> 00:09:43.320
Even if it has a devil drawn on it, they don't mind.

00:09:43.320 --> 00:09:44.020
Am I right?

00:09:44.020 --> 00:09:46.720
These are Muslim children because they are following.

00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:49.320
They will cut their hair like baboons

00:09:49.320 --> 00:09:51.520
in order to look like someone

00:09:51.520 --> 00:09:54.520
who is just able to kick a ball on the globe.

00:09:54.520 --> 00:09:55.620
Allahu akbar.

00:09:55.620 --> 00:09:58.020
For your information, the whole globe is like a ball.

00:09:58.020 --> 00:10:00.820
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:04.020
But when you ask them about the names of the companions

00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:06.720
of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:08.520
very rarely will they give them to you.

00:10:08.520 --> 00:10:11.720
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala use this month of Ramadan

00:10:11.720 --> 00:10:13.720
to motivate us and our children.

00:10:13.720 --> 00:10:16.120
Instead of them sitting and watching cartoons,

00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:18.320
may they be motivated to sit

00:10:18.320 --> 00:10:22.420
and to listen to the seerah of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam.

00:10:22.420 --> 00:10:26.020
Then it is important for us also in our lives

00:10:26.020 --> 00:10:29.220
to look at how we should be as a husband

00:10:29.220 --> 00:10:32.520
because Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam's example was unique.

00:10:32.520 --> 00:10:33.420
Allah says

00:10:33.420 --> 00:10:37.620
لَقَدْ كَانَ لَكُمْ فِي رَسُولِ اللَّهِ

00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:44.120
أُسْوَةٌ حَسَنَةٌ لِمَن كَانَ يَرْجُ اللَّهِ

00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:49.420
لِمَن كَانَ يَرْجُ اللَّهَ وَالْيَوْمَ الْآخِرِ

00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:52.420
وَذَكَرَ اللَّهَ كَفِيرًا

00:10:52.420 --> 00:10:54.320
There is another verse in surah al-ahzab.

00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:55.820
Allah says indeed,

00:10:55.820 --> 00:10:59.020
in the life of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:10:59.020 --> 00:11:02.320
is a perfect example for those who are looking forward

00:11:02.320 --> 00:11:04.920
to the meeting with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:11:04.920 --> 00:11:07.720
and those who are looking forward to the last day.

00:11:07.720 --> 00:11:10.420
How many of us are looking forward to meeting with Allah,

00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:12.920
to meeting with Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:11:12.920 --> 00:11:14.120
and the others?

00:11:14.120 --> 00:11:16.320
A lot of us are clinging to earth

00:11:16.320 --> 00:11:18.020
and we cling to earth in a way

00:11:18.020 --> 00:11:19.920
that we usurp the wealth of people.

00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:24.120
We hate people for no reason besides a few dollars and cents.

00:11:24.120 --> 00:11:24.920
And what happens?

00:11:24.920 --> 00:11:27.420
We stop talking to our own brothers and sisters

00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:29.820
because of some little monetary issue.

00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:31.420
Why should that be the case?

00:11:31.420 --> 00:11:35.520
If you want, here follow the example of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:11:35.520 --> 00:11:37.720
as a husband, as a father,

00:11:37.720 --> 00:11:39.720
as a person who was a leader,

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:42.020
as a man at times of war.

00:11:42.020 --> 00:11:45.620
They say he was just at times of war

00:11:45.620 --> 00:11:48.320
and he was very merciful even at the same time,

00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:49.520
the time of war.

00:11:49.520 --> 00:11:52.520
Look at what happened when he entered Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:11:52.520 --> 00:11:54.320
and he had a vast army.

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:56.220
The people of Makkah were now shocked.

00:11:56.220 --> 00:11:58.120
They looked at the numbers and he says,

00:12:02.220 --> 00:12:04.520
Oh people of Quraysh.

00:12:04.520 --> 00:12:06.020
And they were at his disposal.

00:12:06.020 --> 00:12:07.320
He could have done anything.

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:10.920
Oh you who killed a lot of my companions and relatives.

00:12:10.920 --> 00:12:13.820
What do you think I'm going to do to you today?

00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:15.220
They were silent.

00:12:15.220 --> 00:12:16.420
Some of them answered,

00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:19.120
Well, we hope goodness because you are a good man,

00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:20.320
a son of a good man.

00:12:20.320 --> 00:12:21.820
Suddenly, you know people are good.

00:12:21.820 --> 00:12:24.120
Why? Because now we're at their mercy.

00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:26.520
People become good when you're at their mercy.

00:12:26.520 --> 00:12:29.020
You know, I remember a true story.

00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:31.520
When I was at school, there was a young boy

00:12:31.520 --> 00:12:34.920
and he was so thin and everyone used to bully him.

00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:38.420
So he one day decided in the school holidays

00:12:38.420 --> 00:12:40.420
to inject himself with all the proteins

00:12:40.420 --> 00:12:42.720
and to start pumping weights, literally.

00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:46.220
And he came back just about one and a half months later,

00:12:46.220 --> 00:12:49.820
huge, and he looked at the guys who were bullying him.

00:12:49.820 --> 00:12:51.320
They all started greeting him.

00:12:51.320 --> 00:12:52.620
They all became his friends.

00:12:52.620 --> 00:12:53.220
Why?

00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:55.820
Because he would probably lift them up with one finger.

00:12:55.820 --> 00:12:56.820
Allahu Akbar.

00:12:56.820 --> 00:12:59.020
But moments before that, what happened?

00:12:59.020 --> 00:13:00.720
They used to bully the same youngster.

00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:02.120
Today, he's a big man.

00:13:02.120 --> 00:13:03.920
Nobody dare take his name.

00:13:03.920 --> 00:13:05.320
Why? Because of size.

00:13:05.320 --> 00:13:07.320
So here Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:13:07.320 --> 00:13:08.220
what happened?

00:13:08.220 --> 00:13:09.920
They persecuted them,

00:13:09.920 --> 00:13:12.520
meaning they persecuted him and his companions.

00:13:12.520 --> 00:13:15.020
And the day when he came into Makkah al-Mukarramah,

00:13:15.020 --> 00:13:16.220
do you know what happened?

00:13:16.220 --> 00:13:17.220
He asked them the question,

00:13:17.220 --> 00:13:19.720
What do you think I'm going to do to you today?

00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:20.920
Then he says,

00:13:21.620 --> 00:13:25.420
You guys can carry on.

00:13:25.420 --> 00:13:27.220
You people can carry on.

00:13:27.220 --> 00:13:28.320
You are free.

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:29.820
No retribution today.

00:13:29.820 --> 00:13:32.020
I will tell you what the Prophet Yusuf,

00:13:32.020 --> 00:13:33.720
Joseph may peace be upon him,

00:13:33.720 --> 00:13:35.620
told his brothers.

00:13:38.920 --> 00:13:41.320
I'm holding nothing against you today.

00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:43.520
No retribution, nothing, carry on.

00:13:43.520 --> 00:13:46.720
How many of us can do that to our own brothers

00:13:46.720 --> 00:13:48.920
and sisters and family members?

00:13:48.920 --> 00:13:51.320
I think we as Muslims find it difficult.

00:13:51.320 --> 00:13:53.620
So this is why when we study the Seerah,

00:13:53.620 --> 00:13:56.120
it softens our hearts towards our own people

00:13:56.120 --> 00:13:58.720
and it softens our heart in a way that we learn.

00:13:58.720 --> 00:14:00.720
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:14:00.720 --> 00:14:03.620
he was a judge between people.

00:14:03.620 --> 00:14:05.020
How did he rule?

00:14:05.020 --> 00:14:06.920
He at the same time was a da'i.

00:14:06.920 --> 00:14:08.420
He called people to Islam.

00:14:08.420 --> 00:14:10.620
How did he call people to Islam?

00:14:10.620 --> 00:14:12.120
He called people to goodness.

00:14:12.120 --> 00:14:13.920
We will be going through that.

00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:17.720
He, so many of his companions memorized the Quran.

00:14:17.720 --> 00:14:19.120
How did he achieve that?

00:14:19.120 --> 00:14:20.920
Most of them were adults.

00:14:20.920 --> 00:14:23.720
Today our children are memorizing the Quran masha'Allah.

00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:25.820
We got to beat the daylights out of them

00:14:25.820 --> 00:14:28.620
in order for them to know what is next and so on.

00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:29.620
A lot of the times,

00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:31.820
this is what people think if this all about.

00:14:31.820 --> 00:14:33.920
You find the Sheikh sitting, the Imam sitting

00:14:33.920 --> 00:14:35.120
with one big stick.

00:14:35.120 --> 00:14:38.520
Where was the stick of the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam?

00:14:38.520 --> 00:14:41.220
And yet his students, most of them were adults.

00:14:41.220 --> 00:14:42.520
The sahabah radiallahu anhum,

00:14:42.520 --> 00:14:43.720
what was their age?

00:14:43.720 --> 00:14:44.720
They were adults.

00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:46.020
So adult literacy,

00:14:46.020 --> 00:14:47.420
although they were unlettered,

00:14:48.420 --> 00:14:52.520
look at the love with Nabi sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:14:52.520 --> 00:14:54.820
taught his own people.

00:14:54.820 --> 00:14:57.520
Then we have also through the seerah

00:14:57.520 --> 00:15:00.420
and through the life of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:15:00.420 --> 00:15:03.220
we come to learn the beauty of the Quran,

00:15:03.220 --> 00:15:04.620
the reasons of revelation

00:15:04.620 --> 00:15:05.820
because as you know,

00:15:05.820 --> 00:15:07.620
the Quran was revealed separately.

00:15:07.620 --> 00:15:09.920
It did not come down just in book form,

00:15:09.920 --> 00:15:13.220
23 years over which the Quran was revealed.

00:15:13.220 --> 00:15:14.720
As the incidents occurred,

00:15:14.720 --> 00:15:16.420
verses came down.

00:15:16.520 --> 00:15:17.820
As the incidents occurred,

00:15:17.820 --> 00:15:19.020
the verses came down.

00:15:19.020 --> 00:15:21.420
And this is why it's important to know these stories

00:15:21.420 --> 00:15:23.420
so you would know why the verse came down.

00:15:23.420 --> 00:15:24.920
When you know why the verse came down,

00:15:24.920 --> 00:15:26.320
as you are reciting it,

00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:27.420
you will actually smile

00:15:27.420 --> 00:15:29.020
because now you know names

00:15:29.020 --> 00:15:30.220
and you know places

00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:31.820
and you know why a verse is there.

00:15:31.820 --> 00:15:34.420
And you also know that this verse is a lesson for me

00:15:34.420 --> 00:15:35.620
today in my life.

00:15:35.620 --> 00:15:38.020
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:15:38.020 --> 00:15:40.820
So we have so many things to learn

00:15:40.820 --> 00:15:42.520
from Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:15:42.520 --> 00:15:44.620
Then very important matter,

00:15:44.620 --> 00:15:47.420
how was he with his enemies?

00:15:47.420 --> 00:15:50.020
He had from amongst his own people

00:15:50.020 --> 00:15:52.020
who claimed to be his own people,

00:15:52.020 --> 00:15:53.920
those who were not Muslim,

00:15:53.920 --> 00:15:55.820
but they were just pretending.

00:15:55.820 --> 00:15:59.520
Pretending a man like Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salul.

00:15:59.520 --> 00:16:01.820
He was known as Rasul al-Munafiqin,

00:16:01.820 --> 00:16:03.620
the head of the hypocrites.

00:16:03.620 --> 00:16:05.620
And Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:16:05.620 --> 00:16:09.320
dealt with him in a very very professional way.

00:16:09.320 --> 00:16:11.120
He put him in one corner.

00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:12.320
The man couldn't move this way,

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:13.620
he couldn't move that way.

00:16:14.620 --> 00:16:17.420
Look, even the politicians have a page

00:16:17.420 --> 00:16:20.220
to take from Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:16:20.220 --> 00:16:21.920
How did he deal with his people?

00:16:21.920 --> 00:16:26.320
Imagine, a man unlettered in the middle of a desert,

00:16:26.320 --> 00:16:29.420
in the midst of people who could not read or write.

00:16:35.420 --> 00:16:39.020
It is Allah who sent amongst the unlettered

00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:41.920
a messenger from them.

00:16:42.020 --> 00:16:44.020
That means they were unlettered.

00:16:44.020 --> 00:16:45.820
And He sent a messenger, one of them.

00:16:45.820 --> 00:16:47.420
The bulk of them were unlettered.

00:16:47.420 --> 00:16:50.820
It was a big deal to be able to read and write at that time.

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.020
And Allah says,

00:16:52.020 --> 00:16:55.520
He sent a messenger from amongst them to them.

00:16:55.520 --> 00:16:56.920
The point I'm raising is,

00:16:56.920 --> 00:16:59.720
imagine, desert, unlettered,

00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:02.820
no internet, no phone, no nothing,

00:17:02.820 --> 00:17:04.420
no means of communication,

00:17:04.420 --> 00:17:06.320
no fax, no telex,

00:17:06.320 --> 00:17:09.120
no internet, no television, no nothing.

00:17:09.120 --> 00:17:12.120
And yet, He changed the globe.

00:17:12.120 --> 00:17:14.020
In a few years, today,

00:17:14.020 --> 00:17:16.920
more than 2 billion people follow the message

00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:19.120
of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:17:26.120 --> 00:17:27.820
What powerful man.

00:17:27.820 --> 00:17:30.420
Imagine what rules and regulations he followed.

00:17:30.420 --> 00:17:32.220
They came from Allah.

00:17:32.220 --> 00:17:34.520
And imagine he went to Ta'if, he was persecuted.

00:17:34.520 --> 00:17:36.120
That's another point we learn

00:17:36.120 --> 00:17:38.720
from the Seerah of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:17:38.720 --> 00:17:40.920
Whenever we are in difficulty,

00:17:40.920 --> 00:17:42.720
pick up the pages of the Seerah,

00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:45.120
the history of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:17:45.120 --> 00:17:46.620
read what happened to him.

00:17:46.620 --> 00:17:49.220
You will find that he suffered much more

00:17:49.220 --> 00:17:51.920
than any one of us could ever suffer.

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:55.120
And this is why Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:17:55.120 --> 00:17:59.820
tells us with the blessed lips of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam in a hadith,

00:17:59.820 --> 00:18:03.420
that those who will be tested the most

00:18:03.420 --> 00:18:06.820
are those who are loved more by Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:18:06.820 --> 00:18:08.320
And the next narration says,

00:18:08.320 --> 00:18:12.120
the Prophets of Allah are tested the most.

00:18:12.120 --> 00:18:15.020
And then those who are closest to them in example,

00:18:15.020 --> 00:18:16.720
and then those who are next.

00:18:16.720 --> 00:18:19.820
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam grant us the understanding.

00:18:19.820 --> 00:18:22.320
So when you have problems in your life,

00:18:22.320 --> 00:18:25.220
the way to ease the difficulties,

00:18:25.220 --> 00:18:27.820
to read the Seerah of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:29.320
and I make a dua to Allah,

00:18:29.320 --> 00:18:30.920
I ask Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:33.920
Ya Allah, the people who are suffering across the globe today,

00:18:33.920 --> 00:18:36.620
Ya Allah, and all the sufferings we face as well,

00:18:37.320 --> 00:18:39.520
Ya Allah, grant us ease, Ya Allah.

00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:42.020
The Seerah of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:18:42.020 --> 00:18:46.220
let it be a means of the comforting of our hearts and souls

00:18:46.220 --> 00:18:47.720
going through the pages.

00:18:47.720 --> 00:18:50.420
Let us learn lessons that soothe our souls,

00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:55.720
that extinguish the flame that may be burning within our systems.

00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:58.920
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wasallam grant us goodness.

00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:00.020
So this is the Seerah.

00:19:00.020 --> 00:19:01.220
What a blessed Seerah.

00:19:01.220 --> 00:19:03.620
And it's important for us to create a thirst

00:19:03.620 --> 00:19:06.020
in the hearts and minds of the people

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:09.420
before we actually end up speaking of His blessed birth,

00:19:09.420 --> 00:19:11.220
sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:19:11.220 --> 00:19:13.220
So Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:19:13.220 --> 00:19:14.920
if we take a look,

00:19:14.920 --> 00:19:17.420
his character, his conduct, his belief,

00:19:17.420 --> 00:19:18.620
his acts of worship,

00:19:18.620 --> 00:19:20.520
so much so we will come to learn

00:19:20.520 --> 00:19:23.020
that Aisha radiallahu anha asked him a question,

00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:24.920
O messenger, peace be upon him,

00:19:24.920 --> 00:19:29.220
you stand in Salah at night until your feet are swollen

00:19:29.220 --> 00:19:31.020
and yet you have no sin,

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:32.220
you have been forgiven,

00:19:32.220 --> 00:19:34.120
you are going to be entering Paradise,

00:19:34.120 --> 00:19:36.020
so can't you rest a little bit?

00:19:36.020 --> 00:19:37.620
And he says, O Aisha,

00:19:37.620 --> 00:19:40.020
أَفَلَا أَكُونَ عَبْدًا شَكُورًا

00:19:40.020 --> 00:19:41.220
Can I not be,

00:19:41.220 --> 00:19:44.220
should I not be a slave who is thankful to Allah?

00:19:44.220 --> 00:19:45.320
I know the rank,

00:19:45.320 --> 00:19:46.420
I know the status,

00:19:46.420 --> 00:19:48.220
I've already got Jannah and so on,

00:19:48.220 --> 00:19:50.720
but I want to thank Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:52.320
Today let's be honest.

00:19:52.320 --> 00:19:53.620
Alhamdulillah,

00:19:53.620 --> 00:19:55.020
we do read our Salah,

00:19:55.020 --> 00:19:57.720
but sometimes a bit lazily.

00:19:57.720 --> 00:19:59.420
Sometimes we feel lazy.

00:19:59.420 --> 00:20:01.520
In this cold city of Polokwani,

00:20:01.520 --> 00:20:03.320
ask me how cold I feel.

00:20:03.320 --> 00:20:04.220
Subhanallah,

00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:05.920
coming from a much warmer place,

00:20:05.920 --> 00:20:08.420
north of the border.

00:20:08.420 --> 00:20:09.420
And believe me,

00:20:09.420 --> 00:20:12.520
to make wudu with that cold water is a challenge.

00:20:12.520 --> 00:20:14.420
But look at Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:20:14.420 --> 00:20:17.020
he was already told about his rank,

00:20:17.020 --> 00:20:17.920
he knew it.

00:20:17.920 --> 00:20:19.020
He was a messenger.

00:20:19.020 --> 00:20:21.220
Jibril alayhi salam used to come to him,

00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:24.920
he used to stand in Salah until his feet were swollen.

00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:26.320
Our feet only swell

00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:30.120
when we take a long journey from here to Singapore by air.

00:20:30.120 --> 00:20:31.520
Then you find the feet swelling

00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:34.220
and then we have to rest with our feet up for a while.

00:20:34.220 --> 00:20:38.020
Have our feet ever swollen that much through Salah?

00:20:38.020 --> 00:20:39.020
Let's be honest.

00:20:39.020 --> 00:20:40.320
Still we feel lazy.

00:20:40.320 --> 00:20:41.120
People complain,

00:20:41.120 --> 00:20:42.320
five minutes too much,

00:20:42.320 --> 00:20:43.520
five minutes too little.

00:20:43.520 --> 00:20:44.920
That's the test of Allah.

00:20:44.920 --> 00:20:48.220
If your feet can swell once in your life

00:20:48.220 --> 00:20:49.620
because of Salah,

00:20:49.620 --> 00:20:51.820
wallahi you have followed the example,

00:20:51.820 --> 00:20:53.920
the greatest example in existence.

00:20:53.920 --> 00:20:56.420
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us good health

00:20:56.420 --> 00:20:59.520
and may He make our feet bear the Salah that we read

00:20:59.520 --> 00:21:02.120
because our Salah is no comparison

00:21:02.120 --> 00:21:05.620
to the Salah of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:09.120
So those are the examples we follow.

00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:10.220
His love,

00:21:10.220 --> 00:21:12.020
his purity of the heart,

00:21:12.020 --> 00:21:14.120
his love for sacrifice.

00:21:14.120 --> 00:21:16.120
The sahabah radiallahu anhum,

00:21:16.120 --> 00:21:18.720
if you take a look at those companions,

00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:22.820
99 of them would give their lives

00:21:22.820 --> 00:21:25.220
in order to build the life of one of them.

00:21:25.220 --> 00:21:27.220
I'm sure you know the story of the companions

00:21:27.220 --> 00:21:28.220
during one of the battles

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:30.520
where there was water required,

00:21:30.520 --> 00:21:33.520
one needed it and he saw his brother had a need,

00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:35.220
he passed it.

00:21:35.220 --> 00:21:37.220
And the other one saw his brother had a need,

00:21:37.220 --> 00:21:38.220
he passed it.

00:21:38.220 --> 00:21:40.120
And the other one saw his brother had a need,

00:21:40.120 --> 00:21:40.920
he passed it.

00:21:40.920 --> 00:21:43.220
Until they lost their lives

00:21:43.220 --> 00:21:45.520
in order to save the life of the next man.

00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:46.620
Today,

00:21:46.620 --> 00:21:49.520
99 of us would gather around one man

00:21:49.520 --> 00:21:51.020
in order to destroy him.

00:21:51.020 --> 00:21:52.220
That's the opposite.

00:21:52.220 --> 00:21:53.720
See, totally opposite.

00:21:53.720 --> 00:21:56.120
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us.

00:21:56.120 --> 00:21:57.320
May He grant us

00:21:57.320 --> 00:21:59.120
that selflessness once again,

00:21:59.120 --> 00:22:00.320
where we can sacrifice.

00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:02.720
Allah praises the ansar.

00:22:02.720 --> 00:22:03.520
Allah says

00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:06.520
يُؤْثِرُونَ عَلَى أَنْفُسِهِمْ

00:22:06.520 --> 00:22:09.720
وَلَوْ كَانَ بِهِمْ خَصَاصَهُ

00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:12.720
The companions of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:22:12.720 --> 00:22:14.920
give preference over themselves,

00:22:14.920 --> 00:22:17.520
even if they are in dire need,

00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:20.520
even if they are in dire need of that particular item,

00:22:20.520 --> 00:22:21.920
they would still give it away.

00:22:21.920 --> 00:22:24.120
Today, our zakah, to calculate it,

00:22:24.120 --> 00:22:27.920
we become a little bit stingy.

00:22:27.920 --> 00:22:31.520
What about the sadaqat, the voluntary charities?

00:22:31.520 --> 00:22:32.820
You find small figures.

00:22:32.820 --> 00:22:34.220
Alhamdulillah, it's good.

00:22:34.220 --> 00:22:35.120
It's better than nothing.

00:22:35.120 --> 00:22:38.220
But open your heart, spend.

00:22:38.220 --> 00:22:40.220
And this is why the best dirham,

00:22:40.220 --> 00:22:43.620
the best that is spent in the path of Allah

00:22:43.620 --> 00:22:45.220
subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:45.220 --> 00:22:49.420
is that which you spend whilst you are fearing poverty

00:22:49.420 --> 00:22:50.620
and you're still spending.

00:22:50.620 --> 00:22:52.020
That is now from the heart.

00:22:52.020 --> 00:22:53.120
Allahu akbar.

00:22:53.120 --> 00:22:53.820
When you're fearing,

00:22:53.820 --> 00:22:54.720
hey, I might need this,

00:22:54.720 --> 00:22:56.120
but no, this man needs it more.

00:22:56.220 --> 00:22:58.120
Let me take a little bit of it and give him.

00:22:58.120 --> 00:23:00.320
We sometimes are not even ready to share

00:23:00.320 --> 00:23:02.720
with our own brothers and sisters.

00:23:02.720 --> 00:23:05.520
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deep understanding.

00:23:05.520 --> 00:23:09.120
So now, if you look at Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam's life

00:23:09.120 --> 00:23:12.720
and you look at how the Islamic nation developed,

00:23:12.720 --> 00:23:14.820
you will be able to study it

00:23:14.820 --> 00:23:18.520
and undoubtedly everyone on the globe has a lesson,

00:23:18.520 --> 00:23:20.020
a lesson to learn from it,

00:23:20.020 --> 00:23:23.120
how Islam developed.

00:23:23.120 --> 00:23:26.020
What is it that will develop Islam?

00:23:26.020 --> 00:23:28.520
What is it that will develop the men?

00:23:28.520 --> 00:23:31.020
And what is it that will drop them?

00:23:31.020 --> 00:23:34.120
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not make us

00:23:34.120 --> 00:23:36.220
from amongst those who drop,

00:23:36.220 --> 00:23:38.120
but rather may he make us from those

00:23:38.120 --> 00:23:40.420
who develop ourselves at all times.

00:23:40.420 --> 00:23:43.020
And this is why Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:23:43.020 --> 00:23:45.220
when he speaks about

00:23:45.220 --> 00:23:49.320
granting us power, authority on the earth

00:23:49.320 --> 00:23:52.720
and making us able to fulfill our religion

00:23:52.720 --> 00:23:55.220
without any fear on the globe.

00:23:55.220 --> 00:23:57.120
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:23:57.120 --> 00:24:01.320
قُلْ أَطِيعُ اللَّهَ وَأَطِيعُ الرَّسُولِ

00:24:01.320 --> 00:24:05.020
Say, follow Allah, follow his messenger.

00:24:05.020 --> 00:24:11.520
فَإِنْ تَوَلَّوْ فَإِنَّمَا عَلَيْهِ مَا حُمِّلْ

00:24:11.520 --> 00:24:15.220
وَعَلَيْكُمْ مَا حُمِّلْتُمْ

00:24:15.220 --> 00:24:18.720
وَإِنْ تُطِيعُهُ تَهْتَدُو

00:24:18.720 --> 00:24:24.020
وَمَا عَلَى الرَّسُولِ إِلَّا الْبَلَاغُ الْمُبِينَ

00:24:24.120 --> 00:24:28.120
Beautiful verses where Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala is saying

00:24:28.120 --> 00:24:31.020
that if they turn away,

00:24:31.020 --> 00:24:34.220
then you are responsible for fulfilling your duty,

00:24:34.220 --> 00:24:37.920
they are responsible for fulfilling their duty.

00:24:37.920 --> 00:24:39.620
And if they are to follow,

00:24:39.620 --> 00:24:42.620
subhanallah, Allah will grant them.

00:24:42.620 --> 00:24:44.420
They will be guided.

00:24:44.420 --> 00:24:45.620
And remember,

00:24:45.620 --> 00:24:50.120
the messenger's duty is only to deliver the message.

00:24:50.120 --> 00:24:53.820
Once he delivers the message, it's up to us to take heed.

00:24:53.820 --> 00:24:57.020
And this message is applicable not only today,

00:24:57.020 --> 00:24:58.420
but up to the end of time.

00:24:58.420 --> 00:25:01.020
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us from those

00:25:01.020 --> 00:25:04.420
who appreciate and understand before it is too late.

00:25:04.420 --> 00:25:07.320
And this is why the very next verse Allah says,

00:25:07.320 --> 00:25:15.320
وَعَدَ اللَّهُ الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا مِنْكُمْ وَعَمِلُوا الصَّالِحَاتِ

00:25:15.320 --> 00:25:22.520
لَيَسْتَخْلِفَنَّهُمْ فِي الْأَرْقِ كَمَ اَسْتَخْلَفَ الَّذِينَ مِنْ قَبْنِهِمْ

00:25:22.520 --> 00:25:28.520
Allah has promised those who believe and do good deeds from amongst you,

00:25:28.520 --> 00:25:33.320
that He will grant you authority on land like He did to those before you.

00:25:33.320 --> 00:25:35.320
You believe and you do good deeds.

00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:36.420
And then Allah says,

00:25:36.420 --> 00:25:44.320
and He will make it easy for you to fulfill your duties unto Allah on the earth.

00:25:44.320 --> 00:25:45.420
No fear.

00:25:45.420 --> 00:25:46.520
Alhamdulillah,

00:25:46.520 --> 00:25:51.320
we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to return those days to us.

00:25:51.320 --> 00:25:54.120
Also, what is of utmost importance?

00:25:54.120 --> 00:25:58.550
I would be failing if I did not utter this.

00:25:58.550 --> 00:26:01.050
The qualities of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم,

00:26:01.050 --> 00:26:04.550
we've spoken about his character and conduct and how we will go through it.

00:26:04.550 --> 00:26:08.050
But what about his appearance?

00:26:08.050 --> 00:26:13.150
He was created in such a way that some of his companions describe him.

00:26:13.150 --> 00:26:16.450
Hassan ibn Thabit رضي الله عنه, who was a poet,

00:26:16.450 --> 00:26:20.250
it is reported that from amongst his diwan,

00:26:20.350 --> 00:26:23.050
amongst the poems that he recited,

00:26:23.050 --> 00:26:27.650
one of them was connected to how he says,

00:26:27.650 --> 00:26:33.350
you are so beautiful that it is as though you were created

00:26:33.350 --> 00:26:36.850
according to how you wished to be created.

00:26:36.850 --> 00:26:40.150
Imagine today if I'm sitting here and you know your nose and your eyes

00:26:40.150 --> 00:26:42.550
and you might sit in front of a mirror for a moment and say,

00:26:42.550 --> 00:26:45.650
oh, this is bent and that's straight and this is like this and that's...

00:26:45.650 --> 00:26:46.650
Allah keeps it that way.

00:26:46.650 --> 00:26:48.350
Everyone needs to thank Allah.

00:26:48.350 --> 00:26:50.450
You have your unique identity.

00:26:50.450 --> 00:26:54.150
Sometimes you go and change things, you actually mess things up.

00:26:54.150 --> 00:26:56.550
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى grant us goodness.

00:26:56.550 --> 00:26:57.850
It's your identity, be happy.

00:26:57.850 --> 00:26:59.650
No one notices the small things.

00:26:59.650 --> 00:27:02.750
It's you who notice it more, you're looking too much in the mirror.

00:27:02.750 --> 00:27:04.350
Just remove the mirrors from your home,

00:27:04.350 --> 00:27:06.850
you'll be a happy man, a happy woman more like.

00:27:06.850 --> 00:27:09.150
Allahu Akbar, it happens more to the females.

00:27:09.150 --> 00:27:11.150
So Allah سبحانه وتعالى, well nowadays who knows,

00:27:11.150 --> 00:27:14.450
it can happen to the males also, becoming too conscious.

00:27:14.450 --> 00:27:17.950
So Allah سبحانه وتعالى has created the best of creation

00:27:17.950 --> 00:27:22.950
in such a way that just by looking at him, you would love him.

00:27:22.950 --> 00:27:24.250
Subhanallah.

00:27:24.250 --> 00:27:28.050
Abdullah ibn Salam رضي الله عنه, he was a Jewish rabbi.

00:27:28.050 --> 00:27:30.750
When he saw Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم for the first time,

00:27:30.750 --> 00:27:33.050
he said, as soon as I saw this face,

00:27:33.050 --> 00:27:35.450
I knew this is not the face of a liar.

00:27:35.450 --> 00:27:37.150
This man utters the truth.

00:27:37.150 --> 00:27:39.850
He is the nabi and immediately that same majlis,

00:27:39.850 --> 00:27:42.450
the same sitting, he had accepted Islam

00:27:42.450 --> 00:27:45.350
because he heard the words of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:27:45.350 --> 00:27:47.850
and he said, those are the words of a messenger.

00:27:47.850 --> 00:27:50.650
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى make us truthful.

00:27:50.650 --> 00:27:54.350
And this is why I'd like to mention what Ibn Kathir رحمة الله عليه

00:27:54.350 --> 00:27:57.350
says in the tafseer of the verse,

00:27:57.350 --> 00:28:03.150
سيماهم في وجوههم من أثر السجود

00:28:03.150 --> 00:28:07.850
their signs are on their faces, on their foreheads

00:28:07.850 --> 00:28:10.650
from the sign of sujood.

00:28:10.650 --> 00:28:14.650
You can see it from their faces that this man is pious.

00:28:14.650 --> 00:28:17.050
Ibn Kathir رحمة الله عليه makes mention

00:28:17.150 --> 00:28:19.250
of one of the tafseers.

00:28:19.250 --> 00:28:22.550
And he says, one of the mufassireen have said

00:28:22.550 --> 00:28:24.750
it is connected to your salah.

00:28:24.750 --> 00:28:29.150
من حسنت صلاته في الليل حسن وجهه في النهار

00:28:29.150 --> 00:28:31.750
Whoever's salah is beautiful by night,

00:28:31.750 --> 00:28:34.150
their face becomes beautiful during the day.

00:28:34.150 --> 00:28:35.150
الله أكبر

00:28:35.150 --> 00:28:36.650
People look at you

00:28:36.650 --> 00:28:38.950
and they see mashaAllah the nur on your face.

00:28:38.950 --> 00:28:41.350
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى grant us the nur

00:28:41.350 --> 00:28:43.250
and may He make us from amongst those

00:28:43.250 --> 00:28:45.850
who do not mistaken fair complexion for nur

00:28:45.850 --> 00:28:47.750
because it's a sign of our weakness

00:28:47.750 --> 00:28:49.950
where we think fair in complexion is nur.

00:28:49.950 --> 00:28:52.850
Nay, you can have a man as dark as charcoal

00:28:52.850 --> 00:28:54.150
who is full of nur,

00:28:54.150 --> 00:28:56.450
but it needs one to recognize one.

00:28:56.450 --> 00:28:58.850
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى guide us

00:28:58.850 --> 00:29:00.750
and make us from those who realize.

00:29:00.750 --> 00:29:04.650
So that is the beauty of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:29:04.650 --> 00:29:07.350
وَأَحْسَنُ مِنكَ لَمْ تَرَقَتُ عَيْنِ

00:29:07.350 --> 00:29:08.650
more beautiful than you,

00:29:08.650 --> 00:29:10.250
my eyes have never seen

00:29:10.250 --> 00:29:12.850
وَأَجْمَلُ مِنكَ لَمْ تَلِدِ النِّسَاءُ

00:29:12.850 --> 00:29:14.050
more beautiful than you,

00:29:14.050 --> 00:29:16.650
who the women have never given birth to.

00:29:16.650 --> 00:29:19.250
خُلِغْتَ مُبَرَّأً مِن كُلِّ عَيْبٍ

00:29:19.250 --> 00:29:22.050
You have been created free from all flaws,

00:29:22.050 --> 00:29:23.350
physical flaws.

00:29:23.350 --> 00:29:26.050
كَأَنَّكَ خُلِغْتَ كَمَ تَشَاءُ

00:29:26.050 --> 00:29:28.550
as though you have been created

00:29:28.550 --> 00:29:31.050
how you wanted to be created.

00:29:31.050 --> 00:29:33.950
صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:29:33.950 --> 00:29:35.850
One of the points we learnt last year

00:29:35.850 --> 00:29:37.850
when we were going through the stories

00:29:37.850 --> 00:29:39.050
of the Prophets of Allah

00:29:39.050 --> 00:29:40.650
may peace be upon them all.

00:29:40.650 --> 00:29:43.650
Every one of them was good looking.

00:29:43.650 --> 00:29:46.050
Every one of them had good features.

00:29:46.050 --> 00:29:48.050
Every one of them was chosen

00:29:48.050 --> 00:29:50.950
whilst they had, you know, pure proper health.

00:29:50.950 --> 00:29:53.650
And if there was any little defect

00:29:53.650 --> 00:29:56.650
for example of Musa عليه الصلاة والسلام's tongue

00:29:56.650 --> 00:29:59.650
it was also part of the test of the people.

00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:00.650
Tongue meaning,

00:30:00.650 --> 00:30:02.350
you know Musa عليه الصلاة والسلام

00:30:02.350 --> 00:30:03.950
heard his tongue when he was young.

00:30:03.950 --> 00:30:05.850
So he had a little bit of a stutter.

00:30:05.850 --> 00:30:07.850
That too Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:07.850 --> 00:30:10.350
wanted to send his brother with him.

00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:12.250
And this was the excuse that was used.

00:30:12.250 --> 00:30:13.550
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:13.550 --> 00:30:15.150
grant us a deep understanding.

00:30:15.150 --> 00:30:16.550
One of the reasons is

00:30:16.550 --> 00:30:19.450
imagine if the Anbiya' of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:19.450 --> 00:30:20.850
the messengers were such

00:30:20.850 --> 00:30:23.450
that nobody wanted to look at them.

00:30:23.450 --> 00:30:25.350
If that was the case

00:30:25.350 --> 00:30:25.950
people would say,

00:30:25.950 --> 00:30:26.850
no well that man you know

00:30:26.850 --> 00:30:29.050
the way he is created by you O Allah

00:30:29.050 --> 00:30:31.050
people didn't even want to look at him.

00:30:31.050 --> 00:30:32.450
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:30:32.450 --> 00:30:33.950
not make us such

00:30:33.950 --> 00:30:35.750
that people don't want to look at us.

00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:40.350
With us it's connected to our link with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:30:40.350 --> 00:30:42.150
Then we look at

00:30:42.150 --> 00:30:45.950
very importantly we move on to something.

00:30:45.950 --> 00:30:48.350
The condition of the world at the time

00:30:48.350 --> 00:30:50.050
of Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasalam

00:30:50.050 --> 00:30:51.250
just before his birth.

00:30:51.250 --> 00:30:52.350
What was around?

00:30:52.350 --> 00:30:55.250
You had the Roman Empire.

00:30:55.250 --> 00:30:57.850
The Roman Empire stretched

00:30:57.850 --> 00:30:59.550
Asia, Syria

00:30:59.550 --> 00:31:01.350
what we know as Palestine today

00:31:01.350 --> 00:31:03.550
Egypt, North Africa

00:31:03.550 --> 00:31:06.750
and it had its headquarters

00:31:06.750 --> 00:31:08.850
in the East.

00:31:08.850 --> 00:31:11.650
What is known today as Istanbul

00:31:11.650 --> 00:31:12.950
Turkey

00:31:12.950 --> 00:31:15.350
and it was known at that time as

00:31:15.350 --> 00:31:18.050
Constantinople

00:31:18.050 --> 00:31:19.550
the Byzantine Empire

00:31:19.550 --> 00:31:21.350
was part of the Roman Empire

00:31:21.350 --> 00:31:22.850
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:31:22.850 --> 00:31:26.050
makes mention of this in Surat al-Rum.

00:31:26.050 --> 00:31:27.950
There is a whole surah in the Quran

00:31:27.950 --> 00:31:29.250
named after the Romans.

00:31:29.250 --> 00:31:30.350
They existed at the time.

00:31:30.350 --> 00:31:31.850
They were there

00:31:31.850 --> 00:31:33.150
and who else was there?

00:31:33.150 --> 00:31:34.650
You had the Persians

00:31:34.650 --> 00:31:36.750
in what we know today as Iran.

00:31:36.750 --> 00:31:38.450
The Persians the bulk of them

00:31:38.450 --> 00:31:39.850
were fire worshipers.

00:31:39.850 --> 00:31:41.350
They used to oppress their women

00:31:41.350 --> 00:31:42.850
in a very great way.

00:31:42.850 --> 00:31:44.350
And as for the Romans

00:31:44.350 --> 00:31:45.750
what happened to them?

00:31:45.750 --> 00:31:47.950
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:31:47.950 --> 00:31:49.950
If you take a look at the story of Jesus

00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:51.350
may peace be upon him.

00:31:51.350 --> 00:31:54.350
You will find how the Romans persecuted him

00:31:54.350 --> 00:31:56.450
and how they were tyrants

00:31:56.450 --> 00:31:58.250
and how even the wars

00:31:58.250 --> 00:31:59.850
that happened between them

00:31:59.850 --> 00:32:02.050
they oppressed the working class

00:32:02.050 --> 00:32:03.050
to a great degree.

00:32:03.050 --> 00:32:04.750
There was a lot of strife.

00:32:04.750 --> 00:32:05.950
They were dirty people

00:32:05.950 --> 00:32:08.250
who did not know how to clean themselves.

00:32:08.250 --> 00:32:09.650
Up to very recently

00:32:09.650 --> 00:32:11.950
you find some of the kings of Europe even

00:32:11.950 --> 00:32:13.450
were proud that once a month

00:32:13.450 --> 00:32:15.550
they used to have a bath in public.

00:32:15.550 --> 00:32:17.550
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:32:17.550 --> 00:32:19.250
Once a month you have a bath.

00:32:19.250 --> 00:32:20.850
Allahu Akbar.

00:32:20.850 --> 00:32:23.850
We thank Allah for sending Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:32:23.850 --> 00:32:26.050
It's important for us to make mention of this

00:32:26.050 --> 00:32:28.450
because you won't realize the gift

00:32:28.450 --> 00:32:29.250
that we have

00:32:29.250 --> 00:32:32.250
until you see the darkness that the globe was in.

00:32:32.250 --> 00:32:35.450
A lot of what we see today as civilization

00:32:35.450 --> 00:32:38.050
was brought by Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:32:38.050 --> 00:32:39.850
They don't know.

00:32:39.850 --> 00:32:40.650
Why?

00:32:40.650 --> 00:32:41.650
They hijacked it.

00:32:41.650 --> 00:32:42.450
They took it.

00:32:42.450 --> 00:32:44.550
Then they blamed us to be the hijackers.

00:32:44.550 --> 00:32:45.750
Allahu Akbar.

00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:48.250
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:32:48.250 --> 00:32:50.350
So we have here

00:32:50.350 --> 00:32:51.350
the Persians.

00:32:51.350 --> 00:32:52.750
They used to worship the fire.

00:32:52.750 --> 00:32:55.350
They used to worship many other things.

00:32:55.350 --> 00:32:56.850
From amongst them also

00:32:56.850 --> 00:33:00.150
we had some who worshiped idols

00:33:00.150 --> 00:33:03.150
and some who worshiped people, hierarchy.

00:33:03.150 --> 00:33:06.650
And there were so many different types of confused people.

00:33:06.650 --> 00:33:10.150
If you look at the Romans after a while

00:33:10.150 --> 00:33:12.350
when Christianity came down

00:33:12.350 --> 00:33:14.550
you find every king that came

00:33:14.550 --> 00:33:15.650
he changed the Bible.

00:33:15.650 --> 00:33:17.250
And proudly they would say

00:33:17.250 --> 00:33:19.650
King James version of the Bible.

00:33:19.650 --> 00:33:22.050
That means this is a version of the Bible

00:33:22.050 --> 00:33:23.750
which that king made

00:33:23.750 --> 00:33:24.950
and he brought it forth.

00:33:24.950 --> 00:33:26.550
Then another version of the Bible.

00:33:26.550 --> 00:33:28.450
This man came.

00:33:28.450 --> 00:33:29.450
Another man came.

00:33:29.450 --> 00:33:30.350
He changed it.

00:33:30.350 --> 00:33:31.350
That Pope came.

00:33:31.350 --> 00:33:32.150
He changed it.

00:33:32.150 --> 00:33:36.450
This is why today we have more than 36 different versions of the Bible.

00:33:36.450 --> 00:33:39.650
The Christians themselves cannot unite upon one.

00:33:39.650 --> 00:33:41.750
And we say this with due respect.

00:33:41.750 --> 00:33:43.350
It's a fact.

00:33:43.350 --> 00:33:45.850
So as things were changed

00:33:45.850 --> 00:33:48.550
in order to suit the kings of the time

00:33:48.550 --> 00:33:50.350
there was chaos and confusion.

00:33:50.350 --> 00:33:52.550
People started adding and subtracting

00:33:52.550 --> 00:33:55.250
until they raised Isa A.S.

00:33:55.250 --> 00:33:57.150
or Jesus may peace be upon him

00:33:57.150 --> 00:33:58.650
to the level of Godhood

00:33:58.650 --> 00:34:00.650
and made him part of the trinity.

00:34:00.650 --> 00:34:01.850
For your information

00:34:01.850 --> 00:34:04.750
the Romans also fought

00:34:05.650 --> 00:34:08.450
the Christian denominations fought each other.

00:34:08.450 --> 00:34:11.550
They fought the Coptic Christians in Egypt as well.

00:34:11.550 --> 00:34:12.650
Why?

00:34:12.650 --> 00:34:15.350
Because of who was Jesus?

00:34:15.350 --> 00:34:17.050
Was he a part of a trinity?

00:34:17.050 --> 00:34:18.550
What happened to him?

00:34:18.550 --> 00:34:20.750
So amongst the Christians they began to fight

00:34:20.750 --> 00:34:22.350
because that king added something

00:34:22.350 --> 00:34:23.550
this Pope added something

00:34:23.550 --> 00:34:24.350
this one added

00:34:24.350 --> 00:34:25.150
and the others are saying

00:34:25.150 --> 00:34:27.850
but we don't know what we would term today Bid'ah.

00:34:27.850 --> 00:34:28.650
It's something new.

00:34:28.650 --> 00:34:29.950
It's innovated in the Deen.

00:34:29.950 --> 00:34:30.850
It's come here.

00:34:30.850 --> 00:34:31.750
We need to take it out

00:34:31.750 --> 00:34:33.050
